The paper discusses the application and semantics of hierarchy in declarative business process models, which falls under the scope of software engineering (cs.SE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). It also touches upon the impact of hierarchy on understandability, which is relevant to human-computer interaction (cs.HC). Additionally, the use of cognitive-psychology based framework suggests a focus on machine learning and data mining (cs.LG) or databases (cs.DB).
